s long protected men’s reputations at the expense of women’s sexual autonomy. Sexual violence discourse must have adequate protection if it is to be heard.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aLibel and slanderzCanada. 0aSex crimesxLaw and legislationzCanada. 7aLAW / Defamation.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2024z978311140848408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of British Columbia Complete eBook-Package 2024z978311140825540uhttps://doi.org/10.59962/978077486918840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780774869188423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780774869188/original  a978-3-11-140825-5  University of British Columbia Complete eBook-Package 2024b2024  a978-3-11-140848-4  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2024b2024  aGBV-deGruyter-alles